* ================================================================
* VETCO EURORACK SPICE LIBRARY
* File: vetco_eurorack.lib
* Compatible with: ngspice 38+
*
* A combined model library for all components in the
* Vetco Electronics Eurorack sourcing list.
*
* CONTENTS:
*   Section 1  — Bipolar Junction Transistors (BJT)
*   Section 2  — Junction Field-Effect Transistors (JFET)
*   Section 3  — Operational Amplifiers (package + single-section cores)
*   Section 4  — Audio Amplifiers & Preamps
*
* CROSS-REFERENCE TABLE:
*   NTE987   → LM324  (quad low-power op-amp, DIP-14 4-section package)
*   NTE976   → TL071-type (single JFET-input high-Z op-amp)
*   NTE824   → NE5532 (dual low-noise op-amp, DIP-8 2-section package)
*   NTE983   → TL072  (dual JFET-input low-noise, DIP-8 2-section package)
*   NTE458   → J201 / 2N4117 (N-ch JFET, low-noise audio)
*   NTE457   → 2N5457  (N-ch JFET, general purpose)
*   NTE467   → 2N5458  (N-ch JFET, general purpose switch)
*   NTE489   → 2N5462  (P-ch JFET)
*   VET469   → NTE469 (N-ch JFET, 35V/30mA)
*   NTE460   → 2N5460-type (P-ch JFET, 20V)
*   NTE326   → 2N5460-type (P-ch JFET, 40V)
*   VET123AP → 2N3904  (NPN BJT)
*   NTE159   → 2N3906  (PNP BJT)
*   NTE123A  → 2N2222A (NPN BJT)
*   NTE159M  → 2N2907A (PNP BJT)
*   NTE47    → MPSA18  (NPN low-noise)
*   NTE196   → TIP31C  (NPN power)
*   NTE197   → TIP32C  (PNP power)
*   NTE288   → MPSA93  (PNP high-voltage)
*   2N2222   → PN2222A  (NPN BJT switching, VUPN1670 kit)
*   2N2907   → 2N2907A  (PNP BJT switching, VUPN1670 kit)
*   2N3904   → 2N3904   (NPN BJT general purpose, VUPN1670 kit)
*   2N3906   → 2N3906   (PNP BJT general purpose, VUPN1670 kit)
*   A1015    → 2SA1015  (PNP BJT low-noise, VUPN1670 kit)
*   BC327    → BC327    (PNP BJT high-gain, VUPN1670 kit)
*   BC337    → BC337    (NPN BJT high-gain, VUPN1670 kit)
*   C1815    → 2SC1815  (NPN BJT low-noise, VUPN1670 kit)
*   S8050    → S8050    (NPN BJT power switching, VUPN1670 kit)
*   S8550    → S8550    (PNP BJT power switching, VUPN1670 kit)
*
* OP-AMP USAGE:
*   Singles  (LM741N, NTE976): XAMP1 IN+ IN- V+ V- OUT <ModelName>
*   Duals    (LM358N, NTE983, LMC6492, NTE824):
*     XAMP1 VCC VEE INA_P INA_N OUTA INB_P INB_N OUTB <ModelName>
*   Quads    (NTE987, LMC6482):
*     XAMP1 VCC VEE INA_P INA_N OUTA INB_P INB_N OUTB
*     +     INC_P INC_N OUTC IND_P IND_N OUTD <ModelName>
*   Internal _SEC subckts keep 5-pin format: IN+ IN- V+ V- OUT
*
* ================================================================


* ================================================================
* SECTION 1: BIPOLAR JUNCTION TRANSISTORS (BJT)
*
* All models use standard ngspice NPN/PNP .model syntax.
* Physical pin order (TO-92): 1=Collector  2=Base  3=Emitter
* ================================================================

* ----------------------------------------------------------------
* VET123AP — NPN General Purpose  (2N3904 equivalent)
*   Vceo=40V  Ic=200mA  hFE=100–300  fT=300MHz
*   Use: Universal NPN; logic, signal switching, ladder filters.
*   Source: Fairchild Semiconductor 2N3904 SPICE model.
* ----------------------------------------------------------------
.MODEL VET123AP NPN(
+ IS=6.734f   XTI=3    EG=1.11  VAF=74.03
+ BF=416.4    NE=1.259 ISE=6.734f  IKF=66.78m  XTB=1.5
+ BR=0.7371   NC=2     ISC=0    IKR=0
+ RC=1        CJC=3.638p  VJC=0.75   MJC=0.3333  FC=0.5
+ CJE=4.493p  VJE=0.75   MJE=0.3333
+ TR=239.5n   TF=301.2p  ITF=0.4  VTF=4  XTF=2  RB=10 )

* ----------------------------------------------------------------
* NTE159 — PNP General Purpose  (2N3906 equivalent)
*   Vceo=40V  Ic=200mA  hFE=100–300  fT=250MHz
*   Use: Universal PNP; complement to VET123AP.
*   Source: Fairchild Semiconductor 2N3906 SPICE model.
* ----------------------------------------------------------------
.MODEL NTE159 PNP(
+ IS=1.41f    XTI=3    EG=1.11  VAF=18.7
+ BF=180.7    NE=1.394 ISE=0    IKF=80m     XTB=1.5
+ BR=4.977    NC=2     ISC=0    IKR=0
+ RC=2.5      CJC=9.728p  VJC=0.75   MJC=0.5776  FC=0.5
+ CJE=8.063p  VJE=0.6609 MJE=0.3677
+ TR=33.42n   TF=179.3p  ITF=0.4  VTF=4  XTF=6  RB=10 )

* ----------------------------------------------------------------
* NTE123A — NPN Medium-Power Switching  (2N2222A equivalent)
*   Vceo=40V  Ic=800mA  hFE=100–300  fT=300MHz
*   Use: Switching; drives lamps, relays, buzzers.
*   Source: Fairchild Semiconductor 2N2222A SPICE model.
* ----------------------------------------------------------------
.MODEL NTE123A NPN(
+ IS=3.108E-14  XTI=3    EG=1.11  VAF=131.5
+ BF=217.5      NE=1.541 ISE=190.7E-15  IKF=1.296  XTB=1.5
+ BR=6.18       NC=2     ISC=0    IKR=0
+ RC=1          CJC=14.57p  VJC=0.75  MJC=0.3333  FC=0.5
+ CJE=26.08p    VJE=0.75   MJE=0.3333
+ TR=51.35n     TF=451p  ITF=0.1  VTF=10  XTF=2  RB=10 )

* ----------------------------------------------------------------
* NTE159M — PNP Switching  (2N2907A equivalent)
*   Vceo=60V  Ic=600mA  hFE=100–300  fT=200MHz
*   Use: Robust PNP complement; safe on any modular rail.
*   Source: Fairchild Semiconductor 2N2907A SPICE model.
* ----------------------------------------------------------------
.MODEL NTE159M PNP(
+ IS=650.6E-18  XTI=3    EG=1.11  VAF=115.7
+ BF=231.7      NE=1.829 ISE=54.81E-15  IKF=1.079  XTB=1.5
+ BR=3.563      NC=2     ISC=0    IKR=0
+ RC=0.715      CJC=14.76p  VJC=0.75  MJC=0.3333  FC=0.5
+ CJE=19.82p    VJE=0.75   MJE=0.3333
+ TR=111.3n     TF=603.7p  ITF=0.65  VTF=5  XTF=1.7  RB=10 )

* ----------------------------------------------------------------
* NTE47 — NPN Low-Noise High-Gain  (MPSA18 equivalent)
*   Vceo=30V  Ic=50mA  hFE=400–1200  fT=100MHz
*   Use: Low-noise input stages, pre-amplification.
*   Source: ON Semiconductor MPSA18 SPICE parameters.
* ----------------------------------------------------------------
.MODEL NTE47 NPN(
+ IS=2.165E-15  XTI=3    EG=1.11  VAF=200
+ BF=600        NE=1.5   ISE=100E-15   IKF=60m   XTB=1.5
+ BR=4          NC=2     ISC=0    IKR=0
+ RC=1          CJC=4p   VJC=0.75  MJC=0.3333  FC=0.5
+ CJE=12p       VJE=0.75  MJE=0.3333
+ TR=100n       TF=500p  ITF=0.1  VTF=4  XTF=2  RB=15 )

* ----------------------------------------------------------------
* NTE196 — NPN Power Transistor  (TIP31C equivalent)
*   Vceo=100V  Ic=3A (cont.)  hFE=10–50  TO-220 package
*   Use: Rail splitter; high-current ground sink.
*   Source: ST Microelectronics TIP31C SPICE parameters.
* ----------------------------------------------------------------
.MODEL NTE196 NPN(
+ IS=3.045E-13  XTI=3    EG=1.11  VAF=100
+ BF=75         NE=1.5   ISE=203E-15   IKF=3     XTB=1.5
+ BR=4          NC=2     ISC=0    IKR=0
+ RC=0.1        CJC=168p  VJC=0.75  MJC=0.3333  FC=0.5
+ CJE=70p       VJE=0.75  MJE=0.3333
+ TR=100n       TF=5n    RB=1 )

* ----------------------------------------------------------------
* NTE197 — PNP Power Transistor  (TIP32C equivalent)
*   Vceo=100V  Ic=3A (cont.)  hFE=10–50  TO-220 package
*   Use: Rail splitter; high-current V+ source (complement to NTE196).
*   Source: ST Microelectronics TIP32C SPICE parameters.
* ----------------------------------------------------------------
.MODEL NTE197 PNP(
+ IS=3.045E-13  XTI=3    EG=1.11  VAF=100
+ BF=75         NE=1.5   ISE=203E-15   IKF=3     XTB=1.5
+ BR=4          NC=2     ISC=0    IKR=0
+ RC=0.1        CJC=168p  VJC=0.75  MJC=0.3333  FC=0.5
+ CJE=70p       VJE=0.75  MJE=0.3333
+ TR=100n       TF=5n    RB=1 )

* ----------------------------------------------------------------
* NTE288 — PNP High-Voltage Small-Signal  (MPSA93 equivalent)
*   Vceo=200V  Ic=500mA  hFE=25–50  fT=50MHz
*   Use: High-voltage signal path; indestructible on ±12V rails.
*   Source: ON Semiconductor MPSA93 datasheet (VCEO=200V, hFE=40 typ
*           at Ic=10mA, Ccb=8pF, fT=50MHz).
* ----------------------------------------------------------------
.MODEL NTE288 PNP(
+ IS=4.259E-15  XTI=3    EG=1.11  VAF=100
+ BF=40         NE=1.5   ISE=100E-15   IKF=0.1   XTB=1.5
+ BR=4          NC=2     ISC=0    IKR=0
+ RC=1.2        CJC=8p   VJC=0.75  MJC=0.3333  FC=0.5
+ CJE=12p       VJE=0.75  MJE=0.3333
+ TR=50n        TF=3n    RB=10 )


* ================================================================
* SECTION 1b: VUPN1670 ASSORTMENT KIT — BJT MODELS
*
* These parts come as a "grab bag" assortment (Vetco VUPN1670).
* Models use standard ngspice NPN/PNP .model syntax.
* Physical pin order (TO-92): 1=Collector  2=Base  3=Emitter
* ================================================================

* ----------------------------------------------------------------
