* ================================================================
* SECTION 4: AUDIO AMPLIFIERS & PREAMPS
* ================================================================

* ----------------------------------------------------------------
* LM386 — Low-Voltage Audio Power Amplifier  (Texas Instruments)
*   Supply: 4–12V single-supply   Internal gain = 20x (pins 1,8 open)
*   Output: ~250mW into 8Ω        Output biased at VCC/2
*   Use: Lo-fi headphone output; "accursed" distortion/overdrive.
*
*   Pin mapping for this subcircuit:
*     1=IN+   2=IN-   3=V+   4=GND(V-)   5=OUT
*
*   To increase gain (up to 200x): connect a resistor and cap
*   from pin 1 to pin 8 externally (not modeled here; adjust
*   the EAMP polynomial coefficient manually if needed).
*
*   Source: Simplified behavioral subcircuit capturing key
*           characteristics: 50kΩ Rin, gain=20, VCC/2 bias,
*           ~100Ω Rout, output clamped to within 0.4V of rails.
* ----------------------------------------------------------------
.SUBCKT LM386 1 2 3 4 5
*              IN+ IN- V+ GND OUT
*
* 50 kΩ differential input impedance
RIN   1 2 50K
*
* VCC/2 bias network for output DC level (10kΩ:10kΩ divider)
RMID1 3 10 10K
RMID2 10 4 10K
CMID  10 4 100U
*
* VALUE: Vout_pre = 1*V(mid) + 20*(V(IN+) - V(IN-))
EAMP 20 0 VALUE = {V(10) + 20*(V(1) - V(2))}
*
* Output resistance (~100 Ω)
ROUT 20 5 100
*
* Output clamp: within 0.4V of supply rails
VCLPH 3 96 DC 0.4
VCLPL 97 4 DC 0.4
DCLPH 5 96 DCLAMP
DCLPL 97 5 DCLAMP
.MODEL DCLAMP D(IS=1E-14 RS=0.1)
.ENDS LM386

* ----------------------------------------------------------------
* NTE824 — Dual Low-Noise Op-Amp Preamp  (NE5532 equivalent)  DIP-8
*   Avol≈100dB  GBW=10MHz  SR=9V/µs  En=5nV/√Hz  Rails=±18V
*   Use: High-gain preamp; bringing instruments up to modular levels.
*   Source: Boyle macro model scaled to NE5532 per-section parameters.
*           GA/C2 set for 10MHz GBW; elevated IEE for high SR.
